<doc id="402071" wikidata="Q587107" url="?curid=402071" title="Tiznit">
<text>Tiznit or Tiznet () is a town in the west coast of the Moroccan region of Souss-Massa, founded in 1881 by Alawi Sultan Hassan I. It is the capital of Tiznit Province and recorded a population of 74,699 in the 2014 Moroccan census.

==International relations==
===Twin towns – Sister cities===
Tiznit is twinned with:

* Somerville, Massachusetts, United States (2010) 
* Saint-Denis, France

